cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.CL

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new model for representation learning using gradient boosting decision trees. It also involves joint training of the model using a variant of target propagation across layers. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the proposed model is a deep learning architecture that can learn hierarchical representations, which is a key aspect of cognitive tasks. 

The paper also mentions computer vision as one of the cognitive tasks where multi-layered representation is important, hence it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

As gradient boosting decision trees are commonly used for modeling discrete or tabular data, the paper could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CL (Computation and Language) as these categories often deal with data manipulation and analysis.
